<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 08 at 8:42PM EDT  by NWS NorthernIndiana</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern Putnam,
southeastern Defiance and eastern Paulding Counties through 915 PM
EDT...
At 841 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Paulding, or 9 miles southwest of Defiance, moving east at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph along with heavy downpours. Road
ponding and localized nuisance flooding is possible.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Continental.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
